description.narrative: By the end of 2020, community systems and networks are able to bring an effective support in the communication and participation initiatives for the adoption of essential family practices (EFP) in line with the realization of children's rights., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The rights of children and women are fully integrated into and prioritized in sectoral programming, emergency response, and communication.

description.narrative: Community mobilisation and engagement in 2019 was marked by the organisation of several interpersonal communication activities, media communication and communication campaigns in support of the promotion of essential family practices (EFPs). Meso-level community stakeholders, decentralised partners in the regions, and the media and influencers took an active part in community awareness and social mobilisation. Gender has been considered in all interventions as well as in awareness-raising activities. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
